<figureCitation id="94DEFFE4FFA9FFB51607F934B595F91F" box="[843,930,1717,1739]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1882,1906]" captionTargetBox="[163,1426,194,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-28@20.[151,1436,181,1858]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 12 A–H. Drabescus shillongensis Rao, male genitalia. A, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; B, valve, dorsal view; C, subgenital plate, dorsal view; D, style, connective and aedeagus, ventral view;; E, styles and connective dorsal view; F–G, aedeagus, dorsal and ventral views; H, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479848/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Fig. 12E</figureCitation>
); lateral processes of aedeagal shaft not extending to top of aedeagus in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="94DEFFE4FFA9FFB51750F953B458F93C" box="[540,623,1746,1768]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1882,1906]" captionTargetBox="[163,1426,194,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-28@20.[151,1436,181,1858]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 12 A–H. Drabescus shillongensis Rao, male genitalia. A, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; B, valve, dorsal view; C, subgenital plate, dorsal view; D, style, connective and aedeagus, ventral view;; E, styles and connective dorsal view; F–G, aedeagus, dorsal and ventral views; H, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479848/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Fig. 12F</figureCitation>
).................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="CBE598E2FFA9FFB51199F952B3AAF93C" authority="Rao" authorityName="Rao" box="[1237,1437,1746,1768]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shillongensis">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA9FFB51199F952B358F933" box="[1237,1391,1746,1768]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">D. shillongensis</emphasis>
Rao
